ADDITIONAL NOTICES (do not limit the MIT grant above)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

1. Domain knowledge and skills
   Markdown under knowledge/ and skills/ is provided for research, education,
   and offline agent operations. It is not professional advice. In particular
   it is not financial, investment, legal, medical, planning, customs,
   biosecurity, veterinary, real-estate, or emergency-response advice, and it
   does not create a professional-client relationship.

2. Third-party content
   Snapshots that summarise public websites, policies, or PDFs (including
   government and institutional materials) remain the property of their
   respective rights holders. Fable Offline does not claim ownership of those
   third-party works. Always re-verify against primary official sources.

3. Emergency and safety
   In an emergency in New Zealand, call 111. Agents must not take crime,
   fire, or medical reports as the agent of record.

4. Steam, games, and local soak tests
   Scripts such as scripts/steam_launch.py and scripts/steam_sim_soak.py, and
   notes under knowledge/steam/, help launch games the user already owns and
   has installed, and measure local model performance under concurrent load.
   They are not a game bot, multiplayer cheat, DRM bypass, or tool for
   unauthorised access. Steam and individual games remain the property of
   Valve and the respective publishers/developers. Launch only software you
   are licensed to run.

5. Calendar, mail, meetings, and Zoom
   knowledge/calendar/, skill calendar-mail-meetings, and scripts/ical_parse.py
   support local iCalendar files, meeting prep, draft mail, and join checklists.
   Google Calendar (calendar.google.com), Meet, and related services remain
   Google's property. Zoom Web Client (app.zoom.us/wc/join) and related services
   remain Zoom's property. The Software does not auto-join meetings or send
   mail. Do not commit OAuth tokens, app passwords, Zoom passcodes, or secret
   calendar feed URLs. Prefer knowledge/calendar/_local/ for private material.

6. Windows install media and imaging
   knowledge/windows/ and skill windows-install-prep support licensed Windows 11
   media and DISM/unattend hygiene only. Windows remains Microsoft's property.
   No piracy, cracks, unauthorized redistribution, or fake "Windows 12" rebrand.
   Do not commit product keys.

7. macOS install media
   knowledge/macos/ and skill macos-install-prep summarise Apple's bootable
   installer guidance (support.apple.com 101578 / createinstallmedia) for
   Apple-branded Macs. macOS remains Apple's property. No Hackintosh, cracked
   or torrent installers, or Activation Lock bypass without ownership. Do not
   commit Installer apps, IPSW, FileVault/recovery keys, or Apple ID secrets.
   Re-verify live Apple Support after each macOS release.

8. Social clients, feeds, and RSS
   knowledge/social/, snapchat-web-feed, rss-share, and scripts/rss_share.py
   support legitimate Snapchat Web hygiene and user-owned RSS 2.0 feeds.
   Snapchat remains Snap Inc.'s property. No scraping, credential theft, or
   social automation abuse. Do not commit private feed URLs with secrets.

9. Creative desktop apps and pipeline builds
   creative-pipeline-builds and knowledge/media/ cover licensed Adobe Creative
   Cloud (desktop app), Photoshop, Lightroom, CapCut, and DaVinci Resolve
   templates/presets/exports. No cracks or license bypass. Do not commit
   Adobe passwords, stream keys, or heavy media masters. YouTube Live encoder
   notes require valid access; never commit stream keys.

10. ChromeOS Flex, Google for Education, Minecraft Education, Book Creator,
    Inkstone, and CSS styles media kit
    chromeos-flex-install-prep, google-for-education, minecraft-education-resource-kit,
    book-creator-comics-kit, inkstone-resource-kit (WebNovel Inkstone), and
    css-styles-media-kit (design fingerprints under knowledge/web/). Official
    vendor paths only. Fingerprints are not a rebrand license. No Flex images,
    cracked clients, enrollment tokens, student PII, author sessions, or
    knowledge/web/_local scrapes in public git. Not educational or legal advice.

11. Animation toolkits (2D, stop-motion, 3D) and Roblox Studio
    animation-dev-kit (Krita), stop-motion-dev-kit (Stop Motion Studio and/or
    Cloud Stop Motion), 3d-animation-dev-kit (Blender-first), and
    roblox-studio-resource-kit (create.roblox.com/docs/studio/setup). No cracked
    DCC/Studio. No Fable auto-upload or Roblox cookies. Not careers advice.
    Do not commit huge .kra / SMS / .blend / .rbxl / EXR or student rosters.

12. Automatic prompt generator and swarm prompts
   auto_prompt_generator.py, skill prompt-generator, knowledge/swarm/, and
   Fable --prompt-gen / /prompt-gen produce local system-prompt markdown for
   multi-agent workflows. Not investment advice. Review generated prompts
   before production use. Do not commit secrets into generated_prompts/ dumps
   (gitignored; ship generator + skill only).

